definition.value: A phenotype that affects a cellular process.

label.value: cell wall organization or biogenesis phenotype

definition.value: A phenotype that affects cell wall organization or biogenesis.
A phenotype in which a specific cellular process is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single organism phenotype in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of all or part of the nucleus is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype in which the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cell wall is decreased.
An single species phenotype in which a cell lyses, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost.
An single species phenotype in which an asexual spore lyses, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost.
An single species phenotype in which a vegetative cell lyses, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost.
An single species phenotype in which an asexual spore does not lyse, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost.
A single species phenotype where the slender tubular outgrowth first produced by most spores in germination is abnormal. (GO:0032179)
A single species phenotype where the slender tubular outgrowth first produced by most spores in germination is shorter than normal. (GO:0032179)

A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to hydrogen peroxide. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: altered level of substance in cell

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell differs from normal.

label.value: altered cellular reactive oxygen species level

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell differs from normal.

label.value: decreased cellular reactive oxygen species level

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased cellular reactive oxygen species level

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A pathogen host interaction where the mutualism phenotype is normal (i.e. the same as wild-type), and the wild-type interaction does not exhibit mutualism.
A pathogen colonization of host phenotype which affects the penetration of the pathogen into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism (GO:0044409).
A pathogen host phenotype which affects the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host (e.g. after entry by penetration or infiltration).
A pathogen host phenotype in which the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host is abolished (it was present as is now absent).

label.value: pathogen penetration structure present when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the pathogen specialized host penetration structure is present.

label.value: presence of pathogen growth within host

definition.value: A pathogen host phenotype in which the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host is present.

label.value: abolished formation of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the ability of the pathogen to  form a specialized penetration structure is abolished.
A population phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual spore germination is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of melanin in a cell is normal.

label.value: decreased filamentous growth on host surface

definition.value: A pathogen colonization of host phenotype where the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen on the host surface is decreased.
A phenotype where the degree to which a pathogen (species or strain) is able to cause infectious disease in another organism is abolished on a specific host genotype.
A single species pathogen growth phenotype in which the pathogen specialized host penetration structure is present when assessed for penetration ability on a given experimental substance/membrane.

label.value: abolished pathogen penetration across the barrier

definition.value: A single species pathogen penetration phenotype in in which the ability of the pathogen to  penetrate a given experimental substance/membrane is abolished.

label.value: absent pathogen growth after penetration of the barrier

definition.value: A single species phenotype in which the pathogen's ability to contine to grow after penetration of a given experimental substance/membrane in an in vitro assay is absent.

label.value: present pathogen growth after penetration of the barrier

definition.value: A single species phenotype in which the pathogen's ability to contine to grow after penetration of a given experimental substance/membrane in an in vitro assay is present.
A single organism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer autophagosomes than normal (GO:0005776).

A single organism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ability of the organism to form autophagosomes is abolished (they were present and are now absent) (GO:0005776).
A single organism phenotype in which a protein does not localize to, and is therefore absent from the autophagosome (GO:0005776).

A single organism phenotype that affects a double-membrane-bounded compartment that engulfs endogenous cellular material as well as invading microorganisms to target them to the lytic vacuole/lysosome for degradation as part of macroautophagy (GO:0005776).

A single species population growth phenotype where the rate or extent of the increase in the number of unicellular organisms in the population (i.e organismal growth and reproduction) is lesser than normal.

A single species population growth phenotype where the rate or extent of the increase in the number of unicellular organisms in the population (i.e organismal growth and reproduction) is greater than normal.
A single organism metabolic process phenotype in which the occurrence of lipid droplet degradation (lipolysis) is decreased (GO:0016042 and GO:0005811).
A phenotype in which a population of a single-species shows increased sensitivity to sodium dodecyl sulfate (SDS), manifested as an affect on the extent of population growth. (CHEBI:8984).
A phenotype in which a population of a single-species shows increased sensitivity to sodium chloride, manifested as an affect on the extent of population growth. (CHEBI:26710).
A phenotype in which a population of a single-species shows increased sensitivity to 1,4-dithiothreitol (DTT), manifested as an affect on the extent of population growth. (CHEBI:18320).
A reproductive phenotype where the morphology of the sexual spore is normal (FAO:0000017). The product of meiosis.
A reproductive process phenotype in which meiosis is abnormal. Meiosis refers specifically to the nuclear division phases of a meiotic cell cycle. (GO:0140013).
A reproductive process phenotype in which the meiotic nuclear divisions are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). (GO:0140013).
A reproductive process phenotype in which a cell does not proceed normally through a meiotic cell cycle (GO:0051321).
A reproductive process phenotype in which a cell proceeds normally through a meiotic cell cycle (GO:0051321).

label.value: decreased extent of pathogen-associated host lesions

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion occurs to a lesser extent than normal.

label.value: increased extent of pathogen-associated host lesions

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased level of pathogen protein within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen protein usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of host defense-induced protein

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host protein usually present during infection is higher than normal.
